# 🏥 Health Insurance Cost Predictor (End-to-End ML + AWS Deployment)

This project is a complete **end-to-end Machine Learning system** that predicts health insurance costs based on user attributes such as age, BMI, smoking status, number of children, and more.

It includes the full Data Science lifecycle:
👉 Data Analysis → Feature Engineering → Model Training → Evaluation → Deployment (Streamlit + AWS EC2)

The best model achieves an **R² score of ~0.80**, making it reliable for real-world regression use cases.

---

## 🎯 Problem Statement

Health insurance companies need to estimate medical charges for individuals based on demographic and lifestyle factors.  
This project builds a regression model that predicts insurance costs accurately.

---

## 📊 Dataset Information

| Feature | Description |
|--------|------------|
| age | Age of the individual |
| gender | Male / Female |
| bmi | Body Mass Index |
| children | Number of dependents |
| smoker | Smoking status (yes/no) |
| region | Residential area |
| charges | Insurance cost (Target variable) |

---

## 🔍 Project Pipeline

### 1. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Distribution analysis of features
- Correlation between variables
- Impact of smoking on insurance cost
- BMI vs charges relationship
- Outlier detection

---

### 2. Data Preprocessing
- Label encoding for categorical variables
- Feature scaling using StandardScaler
- Train-test split

Saved artifacts:
- `scalar.pkl`
- `label_encoder_gender.pkl`
- `label_encoder_smoker.pkl`
- `label_encoder_diabetic.pkl`

---

### 3. Model Training
Models compared:
- Linear Regression
- Random Forest Regressor
- Gradient Boosting Regressor

✔ Final Model: **Best performing model saved as `best_model.pkl`**

---

### 4. Model Evaluation

- **R² Score:** ~0.80  
- MAE (Mean Absolute Error)  
- RMSE (Root Mean Squared Error)

---

## 🚀 Deployment

### 💻 Streamlit Web App
An interactive UI where users input details and get real-time insurance cost predictions.

### ▶️ Run locally

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
streamlit run app.py


AWS EC2 Deployment (Production)
The application is deployed on AWS EC2 (Ubuntu Server) to make it publicly accessible.

🔧 Deployment Architecture

Local Machine → AWS EC2 Instance → Streamlit App → Public Internet


## 🌐 Live Demo

The app is deployed on AWS EC2 and can be accessed here:

http://<YOUR_PUBLIC_IP>:8501

> ⚠️ Note: The app runs on a cloud server and may stop if the instance is not running.